metadata.name: GuilCity #264
metadata.description:
GuilCity is the beginning of an exciting journey bringing Guillaume Cornetâ€™s densely-packed cities into the generative realm with the help of Matthewâ€™s (@frostbittenâ€™s) magic touch.

Matthewâ€”with his background in coding and animationâ€”enables a new opportunity to experience these cities like never before. Numerous elements from vehicles to characters and even architecture have been given life. Interact with the city (computer mouse only): poke and peek around (even behind) in this active search & find journey! 

Each generative city fills the composition with the type of whimsical, expressive elements and characters youâ€™ve come to know Guil for. What kinds of wacky features have you discovered yet?

â€”

The tech behind this project utilizes the highly compressed WEBP image format in order to provide so many full-color options. This format is great, but unfortunately Safari on desktop/laptop must be upgraded to at least version 14 and macOS to at least version 11 Big Sur to use it.

The animation system for this project was created from scratch with additional help from the PIXI.js library for individual mesh animations.

â€”

To find out more about your GuilCity, copy your unique operation hash and place it at the end of the following url:
â€¢ https://my.guil.city?fxhash=
(for example: https://my.guil.city?fxhash=ooezL8cffNJGSc4TfNQp3u3WnDpkg8J3zFRczLuumceoYU5QYPs)

â€”


The entire process has been a learning experience for both of us, adapting and exploring the many possibilities to interact with each othersâ€™ skills and ideas.

We really enjoyed building this project together and are excited as we invite you to take a dive into your very own urban playground!

Merci Ã  tous! Cheers!
  - Guillaume Cornet, Matthew Seremet

metadata.name: Plottable Era: (I) Primitive #322
metadata.description:
'Plottable Era: (I) Primitive' is the first generator in the "Era" generators series, highlighting different periods and civilizations. This first series "Primitive" shows the beginning of mankind with people exploring the mountains and traveling on the sea during sunset.

The digital version simulates ink effects and adds a subtle animation over the water. Each outcome is also physically plottable with pens: A SVG file can be exported (right-click save) to plot the piece physically. The plots are designed to be executed in A4 format on either fountain pens (on white paper) or gel pens (Black / Blue).

Thanks to the utility token decoupling, you can get a physical version: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors â€“ as long as NFT is owned at request time.

More details and Source code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-era-primitive

@greweb â€“ 2022 â€“ tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM â€“ CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

reserve is set to previous 2022 physical plot collectors.

metadata.name: Rococo #426
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 150 Â· 100 Â· 70 Â· 50 Â· 40 Â· 35 every 8 minutes. Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Natureâ€™s wild flourish and untamed growth wondrously represent the exacting function of beauty â€” a function that is at once useful and infinitely creative. Perhaps nowhere is this delicate symbiosis better observed than in the flower, wherein a pure balance of physical fundamentals exists beneath ornate patterns and elaborate aesthetics.

Amongst the layers of undulating, vividly colored petals, attention-grabbing stigma and stamen, and lusciously decorative features, natureâ€™s organic abundance and disorder disguises its masterful propensity for precision. Each of the flowerâ€™s components evolve through unpredictable interactions with an unwieldy natural environment, creating spectacular adaptations that emerge from the tension between what attracts.

Rococo painters appreciated the organic fluidity found in flowers and vegetal forms, using their joyful abundance to depict a break from the rigid and stoic period the artists hoped to leave behind. They sought to reframe perfection away from predictability and toward compositions as surprising as the natural world around them.

Thus, â€˜Rococoâ€™ is a generative distortion of an old tradition: a digital painting created entirely with code that interprets and processes the natural worldâ€™s dichotomies. This painting algorithm builds upon natural structures while melding and moving their colors beyond form, growing randomly organic iterations that are as perfect as they are imperfect.

Created by Ori Ben-Shabat & Ronen Tanchum @Phenomenalabs
Creative contributions from Tender @tender_art

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Technical Details:

- Mobile/GPU Intensive
- Press â€œsâ€ to save a .png of the artwork in live view
- Press â€œpâ€ to render a high res output + press â€œsâ€ to save a printable .png

metadata.name: Elemental walks II #16
metadata.description:
"Elemental walks II" is an extended exploration of the interaction and perception of different systems. The generated double grid pattern, the first system, transforms into a crowd of random walkers, this second system moves in random but constrained ways, and with each movement a third system is generated: the texture.

Use the 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 keys to switch between 5 states of movement within the dynamic pattern, you can pause ('p'), speed up ('+') or slow down ('-') the movement. 

Click on the canvas and the colours change within the composition.

'r' to reset position or release the walkers
'p' to toggle pause/play

'1' for vertical movement
'2' for diagonal movement
'3' for horizontal movement
'4' for a second diagonal movement
'5' for vertical and horizontal movement

'-' to slow down
'+' for faster movement

's' save png
'j' save jpg

metadata.name: X Standout #5
metadata.description:
A minimalist work by Nate Donato featuring a repeating pattern of regular black circles. At least one circle deviates from the norm, marking itself as a standout against the uniformity of the rest. Each small difference is highlighted by the brutal minimalism and regularity of the main circle population, as well as the greater collection body itself.

As a further minimalist exercise, minting of this token was heavily restricted to an exclusive access list including only accounts who held one of the author's three previous fxhash collection works before the scheduled release time (one per account, per collection).


--


Live view controls:

Press [1] to view at native size.
Press [2] to view at large detailed size.
Press [0] to return to default view.

Press [s] to download and save as PNG.

metadata.name: Bardez #137
metadata.description:
Bardez is the Armenian word for garden. It is etymologically tied to an ancient word for paradise, but that link goes deeper than etymology. Gardens have always been small pieces of paradise for me, and hearing the word in Armenian triggers a flood of warm memories.

Memories of wandering around my grandfatherâ€™s garden, plucking ripe plums and figs from their branches.
Memories of playing in my parents yard, the scent of jasmine in the summer heat.
Of sun warmed tomatoes in my momâ€™s vegetable patch.
The smell of dirt and grass.
Mud on my hands.
Sun on my skin.
Memories of paradise.

I hope you enjoy these gardens Iâ€™ve planted, and I hope they remind you of some warm and wonderful memories.
 
Nat Sarkissian






Notes:
 - This piece uses a shader to compute the lighting of the terrain in the first frame. If you donâ€™t have a graphics card, you may have difficulty running this.

 - Append â€œ&mag=Nâ€ to the end of the URL in live mode to specify a resolution multiplier. It will render the image N times larger than the size of your window. If you have specified anything greater than 1, a download will start automatically once the rendering is done. The maximum resolution seems to be limited by what your web browser allows. I have been able to output up to 11140px tall and wide using Firefox, which should be enough detail for prints up to 37x37 inches. I recommend keeping the console open while attempting larger renders. It will show you the progress of the render, and also show you if you have attempted too large a render for your system. N can be any positive whole or decimal number greater than or equal to 1.

 - Finally, collectors at the highest tier will be entitled to a signed print of their edition. For further details and updates, keep an eye on my Twitter (@_NatSarkissian).

metadata.name: Ries #294
metadata.description:
Ries is 500 sheets of paper. 
Ries is an cut-up text-artwork.
Ries is artwork generated by an algorithm based on seeded random numbers.
Ries is a digital artwork installed in 5 forms in exhibitions setting.
Ries is an NFT artwork. 

Ries is an artwork where I try bring together my experience of doing gallery exhibitions, my love for generative and copy machine art, DIY-punk aesthetics, NFTâ€™s and chaos. 

The edition of Ries will be installed in different forms and collages in a gallery exhibition in Walden Kunstaustellungen in Berlin in July of 2022. Opening is at 8.7. 19.00, welcome if you are in Berlin.
/www.galerie-walden.de/

The seed idea for the project was the method of cut-up where a text (or something else) is cut into pieces and then rearranged to form something new. A modified Markovâ€™s Chain algorithm makes a small text or a group of words from a pool of texts that include Art texts about cut up technique and generative art talk from tweets. These words form a visual bottom layer and then another layer of words samples the first, cutting it up and thus following the theme of the artwork.

Since the single iterations of the project are designed to be used in a collage, they come in various tone, density, detail and scale. One can test from the variations button and get a sense of what the generator produces. 

Controls in live view:
-Pressing  j exports the current image as jpeg
-Pressing  p  exports the current image as png

To change the detail level one can access the pixel density of render by adding ?pixDens=4 to the end of the URL in live view. You can of course you any number other than 4 also. I it renders just a black image, you have to lower the number, since it is then too large for WEBGL to render.

Designed to be best rendered on desktop Chrome.

Pricing info
22 tez - Includes a gallery shown, signed print sent to minter by mail or by telefax(!)
11 tez - A fair price for an artwork, also the minter can personally pick up a signed gallery shown print from the gallery, after the exhibition.
5 tez - 1/2 fair price
2 tez - bottom dollar

If you minted on lower tiers and would want a print, please contact the artist per twitter dm to â€œupgradeâ€. If you bought secondary, and would want a print, please contact the artist per twitter dm.

Features exist mostly to help with artwork pairing for the collectors.


Markovâ€™s chain code core is based on Markov Me! By https://codepen.io/alexkramerbanjo , MIT License

Displacement shader based on the wonderful shader examples by Adam Ferris


The artist holds the right to use the whole edition of Ries for display purposes for future exhibitions without asking permission or notifying the owners of the NFTâ€™s.

1.7.2022 in Berlin
Antti Pussinen

www.anttipussinen.net
www.twitter.com/antti_pussinen
www.instagram.com/anttipussinen
